{"name": "easyadobeanalytics", "metadata": {"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics", "version": "1.0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/varnitsingh/easyAdobeAnalytics", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pandas", "requests"], "summary": "This is an attempt at a usable python library to query report data from Adobe Analytics 1.4 API.", "upload_time": 1733314162}, "documentation": ["# easyAdobeAnalytics\n\nThis is an attempt at a usable python library to query report data from Adobe Analytics 1.4 API.\n\n# How it works\n* For authentication, you need to retrieve an access token from Adobe using client id and client secret.\n* First step is generating a json structure required by Adobe for querying data.\n* Depending upon if you need segments to be queried individually or not, generate the required number of report descriptions.\n* Next, we submit these reports to Adobe Analytics to ready the reports for us.\n* Once the report is queried, Adobe returns us a `report_id` which we can use to track it's status.\n* If report is not ready yet, we keep checking until it's ready and data is available to be consumed.\n* Once the report is ready (depending upon the size of data), we get the actual report data using the `report_id`.\n* Finally we concatenate all the report data returned to create a single dataframe.\n\n# How to use\n\nInstall the package using:\n```\npip install git+https://github.com/varnitsingh/easyAdobeAnalytics.git\n```\nAll the functionality is behind the `query_and_retrieve` function in the package. Define all the variables required and pass it on. Leave the variable as empty list for `elements,metrics,segments` in case you don't wish to provide one for a report.\n\nExample:\n```\nfrom easyAdobeAnalytics import query_and_retrieve\n\ndef easy_example():\n    client_id = '<your-client-id>'\n    client_secret = '<your-client-secret'\n    company_id = 'company_id'\n    rsid = \"report_suite_id\"\n    elements = ['element_id_1','element_id_2']\n    \n    metrics = ['metric_id_1','metric_id_2']\n    \n    segments = ['segment_id_1','segment_id_2']\n    query_segments_individually = False # True in case you want each segment to be queried individually.\n    date_from = '2024-12-3'\n    date_to = '2024-12-17'\n    date_granularity = \"Day\" # Month, Year\n    report_data = query_and_retrieve(client_id,\n                                     client_secret,\n                                     elements,\n                                     metrics,segments,\n                                     rsid,date_from,\n                                     date_to,\n                                     date_granularity,\n                                     company_id,\n                                     query_segments_individually)\n    print(report_data.head())\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    easy_example()\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics.clean_adobe_response", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics.clean_adobe_response.explode_elements", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "df", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "depth", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "date", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "elems", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "metrics", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Total hours spent: 60"]}, {"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics.clean_adobe_response.explode_no_elements", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "df", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "date", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "metrics", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics.clean_adobe_response.explode_with_stack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "df", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "date", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "elems", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "metrics", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics.clean_adobe_response.json_to_df", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "req", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "elements", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics.query_and_retrieve", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "client_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "client_secret", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "elements", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "metrics", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "segments", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rsid", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "date_from", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "date_to", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "date_granularity", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "company_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "query_segments_individually", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "pd.DataFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "pandas.DataFrame", "project": "pandas"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics.easyAdobeAnalytics", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "easyAdobeAnalytics.easyAdobeAnalytics.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "client_id", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "client_secret", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params":